         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1439">
               <p><persName>Mitchell</persName>, a native of <placeName>Bingley,
                     Yorkshire</placeName>, joined the Methodists after a stint in the army, and
                  served as an exhorter for a couple of years. He joined the ranks of <seg
                     ana="itinerancy">traveling preachers</seg> in <date when="1751">1751</date>,
                  serving faithfully until his death. <persName>Mitchell</persName> was a particular
                  recipient of harassment from anti-Methodist crowds in the early
                  <date>1750</date>s. See Atmore, <hi rend="italic">Memorial</hi>, 274–76; <hi
                     rend="italic">DEB</hi>, 778; and Vickers, <hi rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>,
                  242.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
